The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 16 pilgrims die in bus mishap

 Motihari, Dec. 19 (PTI): At least 16 pilgrims were killed and several injured when the bus carrying them fell into a roadside ditch near Chiljhapti bridge in Bihar?s East Champaran district last night, police said today.

 Superintendent of police Kamal Kishore said while 10 persons died on the spot, six others succumbed at the subdivisional hospital here.

 Two seriously wounded passengers have been referred to Patna Medical College and Hospital while 25 others are receiving treatment at the hospital here.

 The accident took place when the driver of the bus lost control due to the dense fog, sources said.

 The pilgrims were returning from Garhi Mai temple in Nepal and were on their way to Sahebganj in Muzaffarpur district when the accident occurred.




